This package contains the MATLAB source codes for the penalty decomposition method for the sparse logistic regression problem developed in the paper:

"Penalty Decomposition Methods for l0-norm minimization" 
(Lu and Zhang, August 2010)

To run the codes, the users should properly input data and parameters for the function PD_logreg as described below:

% -----  Function:  ----- 
%
% function [x,obj] = PD_logreg(Z,b,Ztype,k,eps,maxit)
%
%------ input ------
%
% Z     - the n x p data matrix
% b     - binary outcomes
% Ztype - `SM' means Z has small or medium number of rows and/or columns; 
%         otherwise, Z is large-scale.
% k     - the desired cardinality (i.e., the number of nonzeros)
% eps   - the tolerance for termination
% maxit - the maximum of number of iterations for running code
%
%------ output ------
%
% x     - approximate sparse solution
% obj   - objective value at x

Zhaosong Lu and Yong Zhang
Department of Mathematics
Simon Fraser University
BC, Canada

August, 2010 
